1.name: Pioneer4you IPV 8 230W TC Box MOD
1.shortDescription: Pioneer4you has unleashed their newest member of the IPV family with the brand new IPV 8. Taking notes from all of its passed successes, the IPV 8 vape MOD provides the user with a quality device that won't break the bank. Firing at an unheard of 230 watts, the IPV8 takes an ergonomic feel and applies the power of the proprietary YiHi SX330-F8 chipset. A spring loaded 510 connector can be used with any 510 threaded sub-ohm tank or RDA. This temperature control compatible device offers compatibility with Ni200 Nickel, Titanium, and SS 304 coils. Loaded with advanced safety features, the IPV 8 provides low voltage, low resistance, high-input voltage, short circuit, temperature overheat and reverse polarity protections. Bask in the glory of these finely designed IPV 8 MODs in black, stainless steel and red. Be sure to buy your Pioneer4you IPV 8 230W TC Box MOD today!
1.longDescription:
What's Included:

  • 1 x Pioneer4you IPV8 230W MOD
  • 1 x MicroUSB Cable
  • Instructional Manual

Specs & Features

  • Dual 18650 High-Amp Battery - (Sold Separate)
  • Advanced YiHi SX330-F8 Chipset Technology
  • Wattage Output Range: 10-230W
  • Joule Output Range: 10-120J
  • Voltage Output Range: 1-7V
  • Minimum Atomizer Resistance: 0.05ohm
  • Temperature Control Range: 212-572F
  • TCR Value: 0.0005-0.007
  • Compatible with Ni200 Nickel, Titanium, and SS 304 Heating Elements
  • Supports SX Pure Heating Elements
  • Temperature Control of Resistance (TCR) Setting
  • Soft Ergonomic Contour
  • Visually Striking Finish - Various Colorways
  • Three Button Operations
  • Intuitive OLED Display
  • Temperature Control Functionality
  • Low Voltage Protection
  • Low Resistance Protection
  • High Input Voltage Warning
  • Short-Circuit Protection
  • Reverse Battery Protection
  • Temperature Overheat Protection
  • Spring-Loaded 510 Connection
WARNING: This is an advanced Item. Please use at your own risk and always use proper precautions and handling as these are very sensitive to charging characteristics and may explode or burn if not properly handled. Please note that there is an inherent risk with the use of any and all rechargeable batteries in any circumstance.
